---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About — Amplified Event Strategy"
  description="Founded in 2015, Amplified Event Strategy is a full-service crypto events agency behind 100+ flagship conferences including CoinDesk Consensus, Solana Breakpoint, Nearcon, and the Ondo Summit."
  bodyClass="inner-page">

  <div class="container-fluid process-section">
    <div class="about-intro">
      <div class="about-intro-photo">
        <img src="/images/work3.png" alt="" />
      </div>
      <div class="about-intro-text">
        <div class="about-bg-text">SINCE 2015</div>
        <div class="lg-text"><span>About Us</span></div>
        <div class="normal-text">
          <p>Amplified Event Strategy has
been the go-to cryptocurrency
events agency since 2015. We’ve produced 100+ crypto
events since our 2015 agency
launch. Our events speak for themselves and we work
entirely by word of mouth.<br /><br /> Weʼre known for launching influential, flagship crypto events, including the original CoinDesk
Consensus in 2015; Solana Breakpoint in 2021 2022; and most recently, the Ondo Summit in
2025.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="process-boxes">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <div class="text-box" data-number="01">
            <div class="title">Founded in Crypto</div>
            <p>We launched in 2015, the same year CoinDesk Consensus was born. We didn't enter the crypto events industry — we helped build it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <div class="text-box" data-number="02">
            <div class="title">Full-Service Production</div>
            <p>From venue contracting and stage design to AV, catering, and signage, we manage every detail so you can stay focused on your audience.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <div class="text-box" data-number="03">
            <div class="title">Word of Mouth, By Design</div>
            <p>We don't advertise. Every client has come to us through a referral. Our track record speaks — and so do our clients.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <div class="text-box" data-number="04">
            <div class="title">Global Reach</div>
            <p>We've produced events on six continents, bringing together the world's most influential crypto founders, investors, and builders in rooms that matter.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <div class="text-box" data-number="05">
            <div class="title">High-Profile Speakers</div>
            <p>We manage speaker pipelines for the biggest names in the industry — from protocol founders to institutional investors to heads of state.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <div class="text-box" data-number="06">
            <div class="title">Flagship Events</div>
            <p>From the original Consensus in 2015 to Solana Breakpoint in 2021–2022 to the Ondo Summit in 2025, we've been behind the events that define the crypto calendar.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="about-photo-strip">
    <div class="aps-photo" style="background-image: url('/images/work2.png')"></div>
    <div class="aps-photo" style="background-image: url('/images/work5.png')"></div>
    <div class="aps-photo" style="background-image: url('/images/work8.png')"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="container-fluid team-section">

    <!-- Desktop carousel -->
    <div class="team-carousel-section">
      <div class="team-carousel-title">The Amplified Team</div>

      <div class="team-carousel-copy">
        <p>Amplified Event Strategy didn't grow from a boardroom — it grew from a shared obsession with getting things right. Lauren Laino brought the legal precision and Wall Street instincts. Zack and Joon arrived with decade-deep credibility in crypto journalism, having shaped the very conversations the industry would later build around. What started as a loose coalition of specialists became something more deliberate: a group of people who believed that great events don't happen by accident.</p>
        <p>The early years were defined by proximity to the moments that mattered most — the first Consensus in 2015, the launch of Solana Breakpoint, NearCon finding its identity. Each event brought new collaborators into the fold. Elaine's meticulous eye for speaker logistics, Olivia's ability to turn sponsorship into genuine partnership, Tricia's gift for holding an operation together under pressure. One by one, the team assembled not through hiring cycles, but through shared experiences in the field.</p>
        <p>Today, that origin still shapes how the team works. There are no rigid silos, no hierarchy that slows decisions down. Everyone at Amplified has been in the room when something went sideways — and knows how to bring it back. That collective memory, built across hundreds of events on multiple continents, is what clients are really hiring when they work with us.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="team-carousel-wrap">
        <div class="carousel-viewport" id="carouselViewport">
          <div class="carousel-track" id="carouselTrack">

            <div class="cc-card"
              data-name="Lauren Laino" data-title="Founder &amp; CEO" data-photo="/images/Lauren.png"
              data-bio="Lauren founded Amplified 11+ years ago and is a former lawyer. She brings 20+ years of conference business and Wall Street event experience. She specializes in event strategy and large scale event production, and helped launch Consensus 2015 and the Solana Breakpoint 2021.">
              <div class="cc-photo"><img src="/images/Lauren.png" alt="Lauren Laino" /></div>
              <div class="cc-name">Lauren Laino</div>
              <div class="cc-role">Founder &amp; CEO</div>
            </div>

            <div class="cc-card"
              data-name="Elaine Cancelliere" data-title="Speaker Management Lead" data-photo="/images/Elaine.png"
              data-bio="Elaine has worked on countless crypto events over the last 7 years, procuring the speaker management system for large scale events such as Solana's Breakpoint, NearCon and CoinDesk's Consensus.">
              <div class="cc-photo"><img src="/images/Elaine.png" alt="Elaine Cancelliere" /></div>
              <div class="cc-name">Elaine Cancelliere</div>
              <div class="cc-role">Speaker Management Lead</div>
            </div>

            <div class="cc-card"
              data-name="Olivia Fore" data-title="Sponsorship Lead" data-photo="/images/Olivia.png"
              data-bio="Olivia has managed and produced live events over the past 12 years across fashion, music festivals, crypto and the cruising industry.">
              <div class="cc-photo"><img src="/images/Olivia.png" alt="Olivia Fore" /></div>
              <div class="cc-name">Olivia Fore</div>
              <div class="cc-role">Sponsorship Lead</div>
            </div>

            <div class="cc-card"
              data-name="Tricia Gallagher" data-title="Production/Ops Lead" data-photo="/images/Tricia.png"
              data-bio="Tricia has 20+ years of event production and management experience. She leads all event ops including site selections, budget management, and acts as a liaison between all teams.">
              <div class="cc-photo"><img src="/images/Tricia.png" alt="Tricia Gallagher" /></div>
              <div class="cc-name">Tricia Gallagher</div>
              <div class="cc-role">Production/Ops Lead</div>
            </div>

            <div class="cc-card"
              data-name="Zack Seward" data-title="Content Lead" data-photo="/images/Zack.png"
              data-bio="Zack ran CoinDesk's news coverage as Deputy Editor-in-Chief until July 2022 before transitioning to conference programming. He still appears daily as a commentator on CoinDesk TV.">
              <div class="cc-photo"><img src="/images/Zack.png" alt="Zack Seward" /></div>
              <div class="cc-name">Zack Seward</div>
              <div class="cc-role">Content Lead</div>
            </div>

            <div class="cc-card"
              data-name="Joon Ian Wong" data-title="Content Lead" data-photo="/images/Joon.png"
              data-bio="In the space since 2013, Joon started CoinDesk Consensus in 2015, expanding it globally in 2019. He co-founded the Association of Cryptocurrency Journalists and Researchers.">
              <div class="cc-photo"><img src="/images/Joon.png" alt="Joon Ian Wong" /></div>
              <div class="cc-name">Joon Ian Wong</div>
              <div class="cc-role">Content Lead</div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Bio panel -->
      <div class="carousel-bio" id="carouselBio">
        <button class="carousel-bio-close" id="carouselBioClose">×</button>
        <div class="cb-photo"><img id="cbPhoto" src="" alt="" /></div>
        <div class="cb-info">
          <div class="cb-name" id="cbName"></div>
          <div class="cb-title" id="cbTitle"></div>
          <p class="cb-bio" id="cbBio"></p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Mobile grid -->
    <div class="team-mobile-grid">
      <div class="tmg-member">
        <div class="tmg-photo"><img src="/images/Lauren.png" alt="Lauren Laino" /></div>
        <div class="tmg-name">Lauren Laino</div>
        <div class="tmg-title">Founder &amp; CEO</div>
        <p>Lauren founded Amplified 11+ years ago and is a former lawyer. She brings 20+ years of conference business and Wall Street event experience. She helped launch Consensus 2015 and the Solana Breakpoint 2021.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tmg-member">
        <div class="tmg-photo"><img src="/images/Elaine.png" alt="Elaine Cancelliere" /></div>
        <div class="tmg-name">Elaine Cancelliere</div>
        <div class="tmg-title">Speaker Management Lead</div>
        <p>Elaine has worked on countless crypto events over the last 7 years, including Solana's Breakpoint, NearCon and CoinDesk's Consensus.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tmg-member">
        <div class="tmg-photo"><img src="/images/Olivia.png" alt="Olivia Fore" /></div>
        <div class="tmg-name">Olivia Fore</div>
        <div class="tmg-title">Sponsorship Lead</div>
        <p>Olivia has managed and produced live events over the past 12 years across fashion, music festivals, crypto and the cruising industry.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tmg-member">
        <div class="tmg-photo"><img src="/images/Tricia.png" alt="Tricia Gallagher" /></div>
        <div class="tmg-name">Tricia Gallagher</div>
        <div class="tmg-title">Production/Ops Lead</div>
        <p>Tricia has 20+ years of event production experience, leading all event ops including site selections, budget management and team liaison.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tmg-member">
        <div class="tmg-photo"><img src="/images/Zack.png" alt="Zack Seward" /></div>
        <div class="tmg-name">Zack Seward</div>
        <div class="tmg-title">Content Lead</div>
        <p>Former Deputy Editor-in-Chief at CoinDesk, Zack transitioned to conference programming in 2022 and still appears daily on CoinDesk TV.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tmg-member">
        <div class="tmg-photo"><img src="/images/Joon.png" alt="Joon Ian Wong" /></div>
        <div class="tmg-name">Joon Ian Wong</div>
        <div class="tmg-title">Content Lead</div>
        <p>In the space since 2013, Joon started CoinDesk Consensus in 2015, expanded it globally in 2019, and co-founded the Association of Cryptocurrency Journalists and Researchers.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <div class="container-fluid history-section">
    <div class="history-inner">
      <div class="history-header">
        <div class="lg-text"><span>A Proven History of Producing "Must-Attend" Industry Events</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="history-grid">
        <div class="history-item">
          <div class="history-year">2013</div>
          <p>Agency launched and has been a long-standing and trusted partner of top Web 3 projects while having Wall Street / institutional event background</p>
        </div>
        <div class="history-item">
          <div class="history-year">2021</div>
          <p>Launched <strong>Messari Mainnet</strong> and <strong>Solana Breakpoint</strong>, the latter with a decentralized format for 2,000 attendees and 5 venues as the first major event post-COVID</p>
        </div>
        <div class="history-item">
          <div class="history-year">2015</div>
          <p>Planned and produced the very first large scale crypto / Web3 conference - the original <strong>CoinDesk Consensus</strong> at the Times Center in NYC</p>
        </div>
        <div class="history-item">
          <div class="history-year">2025</div>
          <p>Launched the <strong>Ondo Summit</strong> in New York City - one of the most hyped events of the year - an invite-only, institutional launch event in February 2025</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container-fluid success-section">
    <div class="success-inner">
      <div class="success-header">
        <div class="lg-text"><span>Success Stories</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="success-body">
        <ul class="success-events">
          <li>Ondo Summit 2025</li>
          <li>HederaCon 2025</li>
          <li>Solana Breakpoint 2021, 2022 events</li>
          <li>Nearcon 2022, 2023, 2024 events</li>
          <li>Chainlink SmartCon 2023, 2024, 2025 events</li>
          <li>Stacks 2022, 2023, 2024, 2025 events</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="success-common">
          <p>While these events and projects are all very different vis-a-vis one another - what do these events have in common:</p>
          <ul class="success-traits">
            <li>Collaboration with our clients to understand the vibe of their project and then bring that vision to life for them!</li>
            <li>Professionally run events - seems easy to say but not as common at Web 3 events and other event producers.</li>
            <li>Clients bring us back year-after-year - we rarely work with a client just once.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="success-logos">
        <div class="logo-holder"><img src="/images/client1.png" alt="Hedera" /></div>
        <div class="logo-holder"><img src="/images/client2.png" alt="Near" /></div>
        <div class="logo-holder"><img src="/images/client3.png" alt="Ondo" /></div>
        <div class="logo-holder"><img src="/images/client4.png" alt="Solana" /></div>
        <div class="logo-holder"><img src="/images/client5.png" alt="Chainlink" /></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container-fluid other-content">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col">
        <div class="lg-text">Have a project<br />for us?</div>
        <div class="normal-text">
          <p>The world's best crypto events started with a single email.<br />Yours could be next.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="btn-holder">
          <a href="#" class="cr-btn black ex-padding">Let's talk</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
<script>
  const track    = document.getElementById('carouselTrack')    as HTMLElement;
  const wrap     = document.getElementById('carouselViewport') as HTMLElement;
  const bio      = document.getElementById('carouselBio')      as HTMLElement;
  const bioClose = document.getElementById('carouselBioClose') as HTMLElement;
  const cbName   = document.getElementById('cbName')           as HTMLElement;
  const cbTitle  = document.getElementById('cbTitle')          as HTMLElement;
  const cbBio    = document.getElementById('cbBio')            as HTMLElement;
  const cbPhoto  = document.getElementById('cbPhoto')          as HTMLImageElement;

  if (track) {
    const origCards = Array.from(track.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('.cc-card'));

    // Duplicate cards for seamless loop
    origCards.forEach(card => {
      const clone = card.cloneNode(true) as HTMLElement;
      clone.setAttribute('aria-hidden', 'true');
      track.appendChild(clone);
    });

    // Measure original set width AFTER clones are added and layout settles
    let originalWidth = 0;
    let x = 0;
    let paused = false;

    function measureWidth() {
      // Sum of all original card widths + their margins
      originalWidth = origCards.reduce((sum, card) => {
        const style = getComputedStyle(card);
        return sum + card.offsetWidth + parseFloat(style.marginRight);
      }, 0);
    }

    function tick() {
      if (!paused) {
        x -= 0.5; // pixels per frame — adjust for speed
        if (x <= -originalWidth) x += originalWidth; // seamless, no reset to 0
        track.style.transform = `translateX(${x}px)`;
      }
      requestAnimationFrame(tick);
    }

    // Pause on hover
    wrap?.addEventListener('mouseenter', () => { paused = true; });
    wrap?.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => { if (!bio.classList.contains('visible')) paused = false; });

    // Click to show bio — delegate to track so clones also respond
    track.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
      const card = (e.target as HTMLElement).closest<HTMLElement>('.cc-card');
      if (!card) return;
      origCards.forEach(c => c.classList.remove('active'));
      const orig = origCards.find(c => c.dataset.name === card.dataset.name);
      if (orig) orig.classList.add('active');
      cbName.textContent  = card.dataset.name  ?? '';
      cbTitle.textContent = card.dataset.title ?? '';
      cbBio.textContent   = card.dataset.bio   ?? '';
      cbPhoto.src         = card.dataset.photo ?? '';
      cbPhoto.alt         = card.dataset.name  ?? '';
      bio.classList.add('visible');
      paused = true;
    });

    bioClose?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      bio.classList.remove('visible');
      origCards.forEach(c => c.classList.remove('active'));
      paused = false;
    });

    // Start after layout
    requestAnimationFrame(() => {
      measureWidth();
      tick();
    });

    window.addEventListener('resize', measureWidth);
  }
</script>
</BaseLayout>
